{"Category": "Diversity/Equity/Inclusion, Social Justice, Gender Studies", "End Date": "Sat, Mar 3, 2018", "Name": "9th Annual Five College Queer Gender + Sexuality Conference", "URL": "https://www.facebook.com/events/2036530993056089/", "Location": "Hampshire College, Amherst, MA", "Time": "All day", "Date": "Fri, Mar 2, 2018", "Organization": "", "Emily: \ud83d\udc4d": "", "Description": "The Five College Queer Gender and Sexuality Conference is an annual conference held in the Five Colleges. It was established in 2009. The Queer Conference strives to provide a safer space for engaging, learning, and fostering community and dialogue through offering a broad spectrum of workshops, panels, performances, and lectures. The topics center gender and sexuality with intersectional lenses, which consider race, class, ability, religion, mental health, survival strategies, and more."},
{"Category": "Science, History, Sustainability", "End Date": "", "Name": "Stories about Seeds: Spring Bulb Show Opening Lecture 2018", "URL": "https://www.smith.edu/about-smith/new-calendar?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D232804513", "Location": "Smith College, Northampton, MA", "Time": "7:30-8:30pm", "Date": "Fri, Mar 2, 2018", "Organization": "Smith College", "Emily: \ud83d\udc4d": "", "Description": "Stories About Seeds\npresented by Tim Johnson,\nDirector of the Botanic Garden of Smith College, \nand former Head of Preservation at Seed Savers Exchange.\nJoin us for a journey through time as we explore the evolution of seeds and the emergence of the angiosperm (\u201cvessel seeded\u201d) plant lineage. These flowering plants arose some 125 million years ago. Learn about how the humble skill of seed saving changed the course of human history and about the current work being done to preserve both biodiversity and cultural identities in seed banks.\nFollowed by a reception at the Lyman Plant House and a preview of the Bulb Show in the illuminated Lyman Conservatory."},
